note: Elite defense meets pedestrian offense. You know what to do here.
Buffalo's defense continues to hound opponents, and this unit has finished as the DST1 in three of seven weeks. BUF DST is a set-and-forget top-5 option every single week.

If not for the Rams and Bills enjoying favorable matchups of their own, Cincy's defense would be the No. 1 play in Week 8. This unit has been far better than expected this season, and the Jets will be starting Mike White at QB. Yikes.

Pittsburgh's defense has been a pretty big letdown this season, and with news that Baker Mayfield will take the field Sunday, this unit gets an additional downgrade. I'm fading Pittsburgh DST this week and calling baloney on the ECR of DST5.

The Chargers' defense has been solid this season, and I'm happy to rank them as DST5 this week against a Pats team that's riding high after whomping the Jets to the tune of 54 points. That ain't gonna happen in Week 8, partner.
